              <div class="project_detail" id="enlightenment">
                <div class="project_description">
                  <h3><a href="http://enlightenment.org" class="external-link">Enlightenment</a></h3>
                  <div class="text_description">
                    <p>“Enlightenment is
                    not just a window manager for Linux/X11 and others, but also a
                    whole suite of libraries to help you create beautiful user
                    interfaces with much less work than doing it the old fashioned way
                    and fighting with traditional toolkits, not to mention a
                    traditional window manager. It covers uses from small mobile
                    devices like phones all the way to powerful multi-core desktops
                    (which are the primary development environment).”</p>
                    <p>I have worked on some of the python bindings (mainly
                    python-elementary) since they are used in aMSN2, but have hacked
                    various bits on both the libraries and the window
                    manager. I also wrote a <a class="external-link"
                      href="https://github.com/billiob/e-tiling" >tiling module for
                      e17</a>. My current involvement on enlightenment is
                    focused on <a class="external-link"
                      href="http://enlightenment.org/p.php?p=about/terminology&l=en">Terminology</a>, a terminal emulator written with
                    the Enlightenment Foundation Libraries.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="project_detail" id="amsn">
                <h3><a href="http://amsn-project.net" class="external-link">aMSN</a></h3>
                <div class="text_description">
                  <ul>
                    <li><p>an open source IM client for the MSN network</p></li>
                    <li><p>written in tcl/tk</p></li>
                    <li><p>works on Linux, *BSD, MacOSX and Windows</p></li>
                    <li><p>got downloaded more than 40 millions times</p></li>
                    <li><p>translated in many languages</p></li>
                    <li><p>…</p></li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="project_detail" id="amsn2">
                <div class="project_description">
                  <h3><a href="http://github.com/amsn/amsn2/" class="external-link">aMSN2</a></h3>
                  <div class="text_description">
                    <ul>
                      <li><p>a complete rewrite of aMSN  the open source IM client for the
                      MSN network</p></li>
                      <li><p>written in Python</p></li>
                      <li><p>based on a multi-frontend approch to be able to run it
                      everywhere. It currently has Gtk, Qt4, EFL, Curses, Cocoa and
                      Web frontends</p></li>
                      <li><p>code occurs on <a href="http://github.com/amsn/amsn2/" class="external-link">github</a></p></li>
                      <li><p>but no release yet, so feel free to fork it and help
                      us!!</p></li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>I'm now the leader on the project and the main developer on the
                    EFL frontend, which explains my involvement in the Enlightenment
                    project.</p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="project_detail" id="bfb">
                <div class="project_description">
                  <h3><a href="http://github.com/billiob/bfb" class="external-link">bfb</a></h3>
                  <div class="text_description">
                    <ul>
                      <li><p>irc bot</p></li>
                      <li><p>written fully in BrainFuck++!!!</p></li>
                      <li><p>configurable!</p></li>
                      <li><p>can welcome new users</p></li>
                      <li><p>supports SSL</p></li>
                      <li><p>released under the Do What The Fuck You Want To Public License</p></li>
                      <li><p>hosted on <a href="http://github.com/billiob/bfb" class="external-link">github</a></p></li>
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

